Below is a clean, standards‑compliant EDXL‑DE envelope that any system can wrap any payload in.

Code
<EDXLDistribution xmlns="urn:oasis:names:tc:emergency:EDXL:DE:1.0">
    <distributionID>{UUID}</distributionID>
    <senderID>{YourSystemIdentifier}</senderID>
    <dateTimeSent>{ISO8601}</dateTimeSent>
    <distributionStatus>Actual</distributionStatus>
    <distributionType>Report</distributionType>

    <recipient>
        <explicitAddress>
            <scheme>urn:edxl:target:agency</scheme>
            <address>{TargetAgency}</address>
        </explicitAddress>
    </recipient>

    <contentObject>
        <contentDescription>{IRD | RRD | Cascade | Lineage}</contentDescription>
        <incidentID>{IncidentIdentifier}</incidentID>

        <contentXML>
            <!-- Insert NIEM or system-specific XML payload here -->
            {PayloadXML}
        </contentXML>
    </contentObject>
</EDXLDistribution>
Notes:

Fully compliant with EDXL‑DE 1.0.

Payload can be NIEM IEPD XML or your internal schema.

Supports multi‑agency routing.
